trans-unit.source: Supplies a hash code for an object, using a custom hash function.
trans-unit.target: Proporciona un código hash para un objeto mediante una función hash personalizada.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> interface is used in conjunction with the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> class.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> interfaz se utiliza junto con la <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> clase.

trans-unit.source: The objects used as keys by a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> object must override the <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> methods.
trans-unit.target: Los objetos utilizados como claves por un <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> objeto debe invalidar el <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> y <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> métodos.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> or the key's implementation of <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> is used as the hash code provider.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> o la implementación de la clave <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> se utiliza como el proveedor de código hash.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> or the key's implementation of <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> is used as the comparer.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> o la implementación de la clave <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> se utiliza como el comparador.

trans-unit.source: However, some overloads of the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> constructor take a parameter that is an <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> implementation, or a parameter that is an <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> implementation, or both.
trans-unit.target: Sin embargo, algunas sobrecargas de la <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> constructor toman un parámetro que es un <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> implementación, o un parámetro que es un <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> implementación, o ambos.

trans-unit.source: If an <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> implementation is passed to the constructor, the <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method of that implementation is used as the hash code provider.
trans-unit.target: Si un <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> implementación se pasa al constructor, el <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> método de dicha implementación se utiliza como el proveedor de código hash.

trans-unit.source: If an <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> implementation is passed to the constructor, the <xref:System.Collections.IComparer.Compare%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method of that implementation is used as the comparer.
trans-unit.target: Si un <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> implementación se pasa al constructor, el <xref:System.Collections.IComparer.Compare%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> método de dicha implementación se utiliza como el comparador.

trans-unit.source: The <see cref="T:System.Object" /> for which a hash code is to be returned.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Object" /> para el que se va a devolver un código hash.

trans-unit.source: Returns a hash code for the specified object.
trans-unit.target: Devuelve un código hash para el objeto especificado.

trans-unit.source: A hash code for the specified object.
trans-unit.target: Código hash para el objeto especificado.

trans-unit.source: The return value from this method must not be persisted for two reasons.
trans-unit.target: El valor devuelto de este método no debe almacenarse por dos motivos.

trans-unit.source: First, the hash function of a class might be altered to generate a better distribution, rendering any values from the old hash function useless.
trans-unit.target: En primer lugar, la función hash de una clase podría modificarse para generar una mejor distribución inútil los valores de la antigua función hash.

trans-unit.source: Second, the default implementation of this class does not guarantee that the same value will be returned by different instances.
trans-unit.target: En segundo lugar, la implementación predeterminada de esta clase no garantiza que se devolverá el mismo valor en instancias diferentes.

trans-unit.source: The type of <paramref name="obj" /> is a reference type and <paramref name="obj" /> is <see langword="null" />.
trans-unit.target: El tipo de <paramref name="obj" /> es un tipo de referencia y <paramref name="obj" /> es <see langword="null" />.
